I don't know if this is new information, but it looks like a resident compiler bug and is not technically a build manager bug:
{code}
$$ build/pack/bin/fsc -d /tmp/ -cp lib/fjbg.jar:lib/msil.jar:lib/jline.jar:/usr/share/ant/lib/ant.jar:build/pack/lib/scala-library.jar `find src/compiler/ -iname "*.scala"`

$$ build/pack/bin/fsc -d /tmp/ -cp lib/fjbg.jar:lib/msil.jar:lib/jline.jar:/usr/share/ant/lib/ant.jar:build/pack/lib/scala-library.jar src/compiler/scala/tools/nsc/Global.scala
scala.tools.nsc.symtab.Symbols$$CyclicReference: illegal cyclic reference involving trait Typers$$class
        at scala.tools.nsc.symtab.Symbols$$Symbol$$$$anonfun$$info$$3.apply(Symbols.scala:734)
        at scala.tools.nsc.symtab.Symbols$$Symbol$$$$anonfun$$info$$3.apply(Symbols.scala:732)
        ...
{code}

There is no error if scalac is used instead of fsc.
